{
  "text": "Ectopic transient expression of GATA4 or GATA6 in ES cells is sufficient to induce ExEn differentiation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Ectopic expression of either GATA4 or GATA6 was sufficient to induce the GFP reporter (Fig. 2Ae,f) , which was detected from 15 hours post-transfection (see Fig.   3363 S2Ba,f in the supplementary material). These data demonstrate that activation of the Pdgfra H2B-GFP/+ reporter occurred concomitant with ExEn specification.",
